I was doing some, um, after-hours shopping in the dumpster behind the
neighborhood elementary school tonight, and I found three wall clocks.
I have two hiding at the scene, and the third is outside in my car.
The one in the car has four wires coming from the back. Two are white,
one is red, and the last one is black. My guess is that the two wires
are for the 120 vac, and that the other two wires are for receiving
synchronization information from a master clock at the school system
headquarters and sharing that information with the other clocks in the
school.

It has a Telechron-looking motor, but nowhere on the face of the clock
does the word &quot;Telechron&quot; appear. The brand name of the clock is
Standard.

I'm not about to plug them in until I know what's what. Does anyone
have some thoughts to share about those wires?

Thanks.
