In the 1950-1960's there were 120 volt clocks with miniature thyratron
tubes. An audible tone was sent in the power line a few minutes before the
hour to trigger the thyratron and minute hand. Maybe it was once a day and
did the hour hand as well, I don't recall. The tone was easily heard in the
building, so at the school radio station, if we were going to record a
commercial, we would wait until we heard the tone, before starting the
recorder. The tone generator must have been a big tube amplifier, but I
never saw it.
