I had a Simplex wall clock from and old mill. It had a single solenoid to
advance the minute hand and three wires.  At minute 59, a cam would trip a
microswitch so the top of the hour pulse came in on the third wire.  Minute
58 consisted of 60 pulses to the second wire so wherever the minute hand was
set, it would ratchet up to 59 and wait for the top of the hour pulse.  I
didn't see any way to sync the hour hand which was on a slip clutch.  I
didn't have the controller so I used an old motor operated timer with a
small power supply to give once per minute pulses.  I made the mistake of
taking it to work and some monkey fingered idiot destroyed it trying to
figure out how to set it when the time changed in the spring.

Ron
